Bolingbroke (west of Koumala) – bushfire as at 8.30pm Tues 1 Sept
Queensland Fire and Emergency Services (QFES) crews are on scene at a bushfire burning near Koumala Bolingbroke Road, west of Koumala. The fire is posing no threat to property at this time. Firefighters are working to control the blaze. A large amount of smoke may affect immediate and surrounding areas including Nebo and Moranbah. Burrum Town (north of Hervey Bay) – bushfire as at 4pm Sun 6 Sep
Queensland Fire and Emergency Services (QFES) crews are on scene at a bushfire burning along Burrum Heads Road, near Burrum Town. This bushfire is currently posing no threat to property. Firefighters are working to contain the fire. Smoke may affect residents in Burrum Town, Howard, Pacific Haven and Buxton. People are asked to close windows and doors and if suffering from a respiratory condition, keep medications close by. Burrum Heads Road is closed at this time; Beelbi Creek Road is accessible. Motorists should drive with caution and to conditions. If residents are concerned their property is under threat, they are advised to call Triple Zero (000) immediately.
